This paper deals with the application of deep neural networks in financial forecasting, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with the evaluation of the models' performance, which could fall under the category of computational finance (cs.CR) or computational economics (cs.CE).
